    <briefdescription>
<para>Main structure holding socket service configuration information. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="structk__work" kindref="compound">k_work</ref> item is created so that when there is data coming to those fds, the <ref refid="structk__work" kindref="compound">k_work</ref> callback is then called. The workqueue can be set NULL in which case system workqueue is used. The service descriptor should be created at built time, and then used as a parameter to register the sockets to be monitored. User should create needed sockets and then setup the poll struct and then register the sockets to be monitored at runtime. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
